The subject deals with the history of Estonia in the 18th-19th century. The subject examines the social, everyday, economic and cultural conditions of Estonia and examines the most important persons and events that influenced the development of Estonian history during the observed period.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce Estonian history in the 18th - 19th centuries through social, economic and historical circumstances.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has completed the course: - has basic knowledge of the background of Estonian history 18-19. century - knows the historiography of Estonian history - knows the most important events, persons and dates in Estonian history - can characterize the development of Estonian history in the observed period
